The paper deals with the fundamental limits of lossless linear analog compression, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the recovery of random vectors from linear measurements, which is a problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP). Additionally, the paper mentions compressed sensing theory, which is a subfield of mathematical modeling (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.MM, and cs.NA, in that order.
